##A Barber in Wuhan, China, sheds tears to cut hair for medical staff

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

What girl doesn't Love Beauty?

Li Ran and Ayaakira work together. China News Service, photo by Anyuan District

China News Service correspondent Xia Chunping

Today is Valentine's Day, and Ayaakira and Li ran have arranged to go to the Cabinetsungju hotel in New York to give free haircuts to the medical team staying there.

Ayaakira, 30, and his partner, Li ran, 24, are barbers at In Style Han Street, a popular salon chain In Wuhan. In recent days, they drive around the country to support the Wuhan Epidemic area medical team to stay in Vienna hotel, Golden Shield Hotel in Guanggu and other places, for more than 150 medical staff haircuts.

Ayaakira, from Gushi County in Henan Province, has worked in Wuhan for 12 years, claiming to be "Half Wuhan" and now works as a senior barber. He told China News Service: "These medical staff rushed from all over Wuhan to the epidemic prevention and control line to wear thick protective clothing, long hair is really inconvenient. ". But I've had my hair cut for more than 10 years, and I've never had a young woman ask for a shave. The night before last, when I was cutting hair for Hebei medical team members in the lobby of the Hankou Vienna Hotel, a waist-length sister told me as soon as she sat down on a stool: 'Shave your head! ' " 

"I thought I heard it wrong! " Ayaakira told reporters. "when I picked up the scissors and stroked her long, glossy black hair, I asked her again, 'are you sure you're bald? ' The older sister hesitated for a moment and then sobbed, 'Bald! ' I couldn't help but have red circles under my eyes and was affected by the older sister's behavior. "

Ayaakira gets his hair cut by Anyuan District, China News Service

AYAAKIRA's girlfriend, Li ran, was a quiet, beautiful woman from Ensch, Hubei Province, who had been a barber for eight years. From the beginning of the shampoo handyman to now is also a skilled hairdresser. Cut, Perm, dye, hair sample can afford. These days, Li ran and her boyfriend went to the hotel to cut the hair of the medical staff.

As a woman, Li said, she has never advised women to get a buzz cut or to go bald. Which girl does not love beauty, and which beauty of girls do not want to have a head of long hair, women's hair is to the waist, shoulder-length, the shortest is the ear. His hand shook as he shaved the head of a female Xinjiang medical team member yesterday at the Golden Shield Hotel in Wuchang's Guanggu district. When Li ran first cut the paramedic's long hair to her ears, ready to push the scissors on her head to push the first cut, the girl cried.

"I have never seen such a scene, quite admire the courage of this sister. At that moment, I seemed to feel that I had grown up and had a deeper understanding of life! " Li Ran told reporters.

Photograph by Anyuan District, China News Service

Ayaakira and his girlfriend, Li ran, had planned to stay open during the Spring Festival at a Wuhan barbershop, and return home with their girlfriend for the Lunar New Year to the Lantern Festival after the eighth day of the Lunar New Year and other employees return to work. However, on January 23, Wuhan was closed because it cut off the transmission of the new coronavirus. Ayaakira told reporters that a few days ago, a friend in Wechat friend circle message, called for Wuhan to support anti-epidemic treatment of medical staff haircut. As soon as he and his girlfriend discussed it, they decided to join the voluntary haircutting activities. These days, together with his girlfriend and other colleagues, he formed a voluntary haircutting team, driving their own cars, with a simple haircutting tools on the medical team to check into the hotel. They drove to the hotel every day from 6 pm and worked nonstop until midnight, each managing 20 to 30 people a night.

"We think of the hotel lobby as a barber shop, and some of the hotel lobbies don't have mirrors, so we use them as mirrors against the glass doors of the lobby, " Ayaakira said.

Ayaakira told reporters that the medical team haircut, men are basically bald, buzz cut, short hair, some women from the waist, chest-length hair cut to bald, ear-length hair, chopped hair.

The Salon where Ayaakira and Li worked was a trendy boutique for young people, and the prices were high, ranging from 150 to 280 yuan for a haircut.

"There's a difference between a haircut, a good deed and a day-to-day fee. We feel more fulfilled when we give free haircuts to medical staff who have come all the way to China to help us. This is also our contribution to the fight against the 'epidemic' . We will hold out until the epidemic is over,"Ayaakira said, "Now our barbershop is closed and we don't have a source of income for the time being, but we will carry it for as long as we can. Hopefully it will be over soon. "
